### **Common Commands**

**Training**

```bash
conda run -n ms bash scripts/run_new_train.sh
```

**Inference**

```bash
conda run -n ms python -m src_new.inference \
  --config configs/config.yaml \
  --checkpoint checkpoints/last.ckpt \
  --image assets/sample.jpg
```

**Testing**

```bash
conda run -n ms pytest tests/rl/test_prompt_batch_smoke.py -v
```

**Data Conversion**

```bash
conda run -n ms bash data_conversion/convert_dataset.sh
```

**Command Construction**
- Always send commands as **single, complete lines**
- Avoid line breaks within command strings
- Use proper quoting when paths contain spaces
